  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In an upcoming version of MetaMask (likely shipping in the next 7 to 14 days), we are making a breaking change to the return value of `wallet_getPermissions` and `wallet_requestPermissions`. Specifically, caveat names will be removed, and the type of the caveat that contains the complete list of the user's exposed accounts will change. MyCrypto makes use of the current return value e.g. [here](https://github.com/MyCryptoHQ/MyCrypto/blob/master/src/services/EthService/web3/node.ts#L98-L100).\r\n\r\nThe good news is that migration can occur at any time. For example, to fix the above snippet, simple change it from:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n  const exposedAccounts = walletPermissions.find(\r\n    (caveat: any) => caveat.name === 'exposedAccounts'\r\n  ) as IExposedAccountsPermission | undefined;\r\n```\r\n\r\nto:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n  const exposedAccounts = walletPermissions.find(\r\n    (caveat: any) => caveat.name === 'exposedAccounts' || caveat.type === 'restrictReturnedAccounts'\r\n  ) as IExposedAccountsPermission | undefined;\r\n```\r\n\r\nand it will be compatible with both the current state of affairs and the upcoming breaking change.\r\n\r\nWe apologize for the inconvenience. If you have any questions, please let us know!",
